{"id":70525,"date":"2020-03-08T16:46:43","date_gmt":"2020-03-08T23:46:43","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/?p=70525"},"modified":"2021-05-12T23:06:31","modified_gmt":"2021-05-13T06:06:31","slug":"american-universities-move-to-online-classes-due-to-coronavirus","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/american-universities-move-to-online-classes-due-to-coronavirus\/","title":{"rendered":"American Universities Move to Online Classes Due to Coronavirus"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/Coronaviruses_004_lores.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-70527\" src=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/Coronaviruses_004_lores.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1368\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/Coronaviruses_004_lores.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/Coronaviruses_004_lores-300x214.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/Coronaviruses_004_lores-768x547.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/Coronaviruses_004_lores-1024x730.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" \/><\/a>Six American universities have cancelled in-person classes and are moving instruction online in response to the Coronavirus. <a href=\"https:\/\/news.stanford.edu\/2020\/03\/06\/letter-provost-drell-covid-19-updates-online-classes-admit-weekend\/\">Stanford University<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bostonglobe.com\/2020\/03\/07\/nation\/coronavirus-prompts-northeastern-move-online-teaching-seattle-foreign-students-could-lose-visas\/\">Northeastern University\u2019s Seattle Campus<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sandiegouniontribune.com\/news\/education\/story\/2020-03-06\/classes-canceled-at-brandman-universitys-san-diego-campus-due-to-concerns-about-coronavirus\">Brandman University<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.seattleu.edu\/coronavirus\/beginning-march-9-classes-and-finals-will-not-be-held-in-person.html\">Seattle University<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/spu.edu\/about-spu\/press-room\/Press\/spu-winter-quarter-classes-online\">Seattle Pacific University<\/a>, and the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.washington.edu\/coronavirus\/2020\/03\/06\/moving-classes-online-and-concluding-the-winter-quarter\/\">University of Washington<\/a> all announced closures on March 6th and 7th.<\/p>\n<p>Many other universities are preparing for the possibility of cancelling in person classes. Harvard University administrators asked its faculty to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.thecrimson.com\/article\/2020\/3\/4\/faculty-discuss-coronavirus\/\">familiarize themselves with Zoom<\/a>, an online video conferencing platform.<\/p>\n<p>Online classes saw <a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/china-moocs-coronavirus\/\">widespread adoption in China<\/a>, Class Central reported, but American universities had not taken similar steps in response to the Coronavirus until recently.<\/p>\n<p>In general, the transition to online instruction is unlikely to be smooth given the short timeframe instructors have to make the switch. Stanford University put together a website titled \u201c<a href=\"https:\/\/teachanywhere.stanford.edu\">Teach Anywhere<\/a>\u201d listing advice and resources for instructors. The website <a href=\"https:\/\/teachanywhere.stanford.edu\/best-practices\">recommends using video conferencing tools<\/a> like Zoom as an alternative to delivering in-person lectures. However, noting that \u201cscheduling can be a problem, and only a few students will actively participate (just like in your classroom),\u201d the website recommends that instructors use asynchronous communication tools, like discussion boards, when possible.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Six American universit